[Belgium has been officially free from bovine tuberculosis for 10 years, though sporadic cases still occur.

The requirements for a country to qualify as free from bTB are stipulated in OIE's terrestrial Code, article 11.6.2., available at http://www.oie.int/index.php?id=169&L=0&htmfile=chapitre_bovine_tuberculosis_farmed_cervidae.htm. As long as the country maintains its bTB-freedom in at least 99.8 per cent of the herds and 99.9 per cent of the cattle, its national bTB-free status recognition is maintained.

Final results of the tests within the remaining 101 contact farms, and information on the initial source of infection, are anticipated. - Mod.AS

Maps of Belgium can be seen at http://www.mapsofworld.com/belgium/maps/belgium-political-map.jpg and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3587763,27639. - Sr.Tech.Ed.MJ]
